        <body>
            <entry xml:id="entry_irux" xml:lang="os-x-digor">
                <form type="lemma"><orth>irux</orth></form>
                <usg><lang/></usg>
                <sense><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>лицо</q>
                        </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>face</q>
                        </abv:tr></sense><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>внимание</q>
                        </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>attention</q>
                        </abv:tr></sense></sense>
                <re xml:lang="os-x-digor">
                    <lang/>
                    <form type="lemma"><orth>irux æzdaxun</orth></form>
                    <sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>поворачиваться лицом к чему или кому-либо</q>
                        </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>to turn one's face towards someone or something</q>
                        </abv:tr></sense>
                    <note type="comment" xml:lang="ru"> (= и. %iærgom yzdaxyn%i)</note>
                    <note type="comment" xml:lang="en"> (= Iron %iærgom yzdaxyn%i)</note>
                </re>
                <abv:exampleGrp>
                    <abv:example>
                        <quote>е ’rux ku razdaxa æ xæʒarærdæmæ...</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>когда он повернет лицо к своему дому...</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>when he turned his face to his house ...</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_СОПам."/><biblScope>II
                            17</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example>
                        <quote>e ʼrux næ xatuj</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>не обращает внимания</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>s/he does not pay attention</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_СОПам."/><biblScope>II
                            107</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                </abv:exampleGrp>
                <etym xml:lang="ru">Вероятно, восходит к <mentioned xml:lang="ira"><lang/>
                        <w>*ruka-, *rauka-</w>
                        <gloss><q>свет</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ira"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>светлый</q></gloss></mentioned> и пр.; ср. <mentioned
                        xml:lang="sa"><lang/>
                        <w>roka-</w>
                        <gloss><q>свет</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"
                            ><w>loka-</w>
                        <gloss><q>открытое пространство</q></gloss></mentioned>. Семантика ‘лица’
                    ведет в этом случае к понятию ‘светлого’, ‘ясного’, ‘открытого’. Точно такое же
                    развитие значения в %bавестийском%b: <mentioned xml:lang="ae"><lang/>
                        <w>čivra-</w>
                        <gloss><q>светлый</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ae"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>ясный</q></gloss></mentioned> (<mentioned xml:lang="sa"><lang/>
                        <w>čitra-</w>
                        <gloss><q>светлый</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>сияющий</q></gloss></mentioned>) → ‘лицо’. Ср. также ос. <ref
                        type="xr" target="#entry_ærgom"/> ‘явный’ → ‘лицо’. Начальный %ii%i в
                    %iirux%i представляет определенный артикль %ii%i, слившийся с именем *%irux%i.
                    %bПерс.%b <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><lang/>
                        <w>rux</w>
                        <gloss><q>лицо</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>щека</q></gloss></mentioned>, возможно, одного происхождения с ос.
                    %iirux%i (см. <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Horn._Gr."
                            /><biblScope>136</biblScope></bibl>). См. <ref type="xr"
                        target="#entry_rūs"/> | %iros%i ‘щека’.</etym>
                <etym xml:lang="en">It probably traces back to <mentioned xml:lang="ira"><lang/>
                        <w>*ruka-, *rauka-</w>
                        <gloss><q>light</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ira"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>bright</q></gloss></mentioned> etc.; cf. <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><lang/>
                        <w>roka-</w>
                        <gloss><q>light</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"
                            ><w>loka-</w>
                        <gloss><q>open space</q></gloss></mentioned>. The semantics of ‘face’ leads
                    in this case to the meaning ‘light’, ‘clear’, ‘open’. The same evolution of the
                    meaning in %bAvestan%b: <mentioned xml:lang="ae"><lang/>
                        <w>čivra-</w>
                        <gloss><q>light</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ae"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>bright</q></gloss></mentioned> (<mentioned xml:lang="sa"><lang/>
                        <w>čitra-</w>
                        <gloss><q>light</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>shining</q></gloss></mentioned>) → ‘face’. Cf. also Ossetic <ref
                        type="xr" target="#entry_ærgom"/> ‘evident’ → ‘face’. The initial %ii%i in
                    %iirux%i is a definite article %ii%i, fused with the noun *%irux%i. <mentioned
                        xml:lang="fa"><lang/>
                        <w>rux</w>
                        <gloss><q>face</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>cheek</q></gloss></mentioned>, is probably of one origin with
                    Ossetic %iirux%i (see <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Horn._Gr."
                            /><biblScope>136</biblScope></bibl>). See <ref type="xr"
                        target="#entry_rūs"/> | %iros%i ‘cheek’.</etym>
            </entry>
